			<title>Mega Man 9</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?78401-Mega-Man-9&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 18 Jan 2016 04:08:16 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[Since I got a ps3 last year for Dark Souls, I finally got around to playing Mega Man 9 (http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?76583-The-One-Game-that-Needs-an-8-bit-Retrofit). 
 
I've only played a few hours at this point, but it's fun.  It took awhile to get used to, it felt like I was...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Since I got a ps3 last year for Dark Souls, I finally got around to playing <a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?76583-The-One-Game-that-Needs-an-8-bit-Retrofit" target="_blank">Mega Man 9</a>.<br />
<br />
I've only played a few hours at this point, but it's fun.  It took awhile to get used to, it felt like I was beating my head against the wall for awhile until I finally beat Galaxy Man, and Hornet Man shortly after that (when I realized you could buy multiple energy tanks).  In general level design is very good, and flows just like the classic Mega Man games.<br />
<br />
I enjoy the difficulty except for one aspect: the insta-death platforming sections, especially if they involve ceiling spikes.  For me, there's too many and they are too tricky for how early in the game they are (sometimes before you even get to the level midpoint).  Occasionally, I don't mind getting stumped by a hard jump, but when there are 2-4+ tricky instant death jumps in every level I just start feeling annoyed at having to constantly repeat sections of the game because I held the jump button down just a tiny bit too long.  Beat Call and Spike Guard help a little, but only a very little since you can't save them to enable when you really want them.<br />
<br />
So far, Hornet Man, Jewel Man, Splash Woman and Tornado Man all have ceiling spikes and tricky platforming.  Plug man is the disappearing blocks level.  Magma Man is full of lava pits (though I have only tried his stage once so far).</div>

]]></content:encoded>
